              <h2>Who our clients are</h2>
              <p><img src="./images/produce_200_150.jpg" class="right-image"/>Not everyone will be a good fit as our client, and we’re cool with that. If you don’t cook or already have a bountiful garden, we honestly won’t be right for you. If you love having the highest quality ingredients while you cook, or if you want to make a positive impact on this planet’s ecosystems, we’re off to a good start! You don’t need to be a seasoned gardener or landscape designer though, that’s where we can help.</p>
              <p>As a Nightshade client, you’ll become a plant-growing badass with the help of our hands-on training sessions, and most importantly, you’ll get the multitude of benefits that come alongside an attractive and practical outdoor space that enhances your culinary prowess.</p>
              <p>Our mission is to find and create mutually beneficial relationships with folks who have a shared passion for quality food/drink, and an appreciation and sense of responsibility for the future of our planet.  Once we find clients that are a good match for Nightshade, we work our butts off to deliver a high quality garden and provide you with on-going support. If you’re interested in learning more about becoming a client, check out our <a href="./contact">CONTACT US</a> page.</p>
